  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd   \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Police are looking for Singaravel's relatives",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Maskelia police have requested that a healthy person died after being admitted to the hospital at a bus stand near Maskelia-Lakambay market road under Maskelia police division.",
        "Police said that the deceased has been identified as 75-year-old Angamuthu Singaravel.",
        "He was 163 meters tall and was wearing a blue long shirt and a blue saree when he was admitted to the hospital, police said.",
        "He had been living with his son in Lakhambe area from 1980-85, but later they both left the area and the wife of the deceased was a teacher.",
        "While his body has been kept in the mortuary of Dikoya Klangan Hospital, the Maskelia police have said that they have sought the help of the public to hand over the body to the relatives.",
        "Therefore, those who have information regarding the relatives of the deceased have been requested to provide information to Maskelia Police Station Chief Police Inspector Ariyaratne on mobile number 0718591126 or 052-2277222."
      ],
